    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_PersonalizationPerUser_ResetPageSettings",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to reset personalization settings for a specific user and page within a given application. It achieves this by deleting entries from the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_PersonalizationPerUser",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table that match the specified user and page path, effectively removing any personalized settings for that user-page combination. Additionally, it updates the user's last activity date to the current time."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves multiple database operations, including selecting identifiers, updating user activity, and deleting records. It also includes conditional logic to handle cases where the application, path, or user does not exist. The complexity is medium due to the combination of these operations and the need to handle potential null values and ensure data integrity."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
